Manual attendance mark/override page

Completes the spec section 3 "mark / override attendance" capability and
lights up the last greyed "Attendance" nav stub.

- /attendance: daily per-site grid of active workers with inline In/Out time
  fields. Set In to mark present; add Out to compute total + overtime
  (-> pending). Handles failed scans, missed clock-outs, and corrections.
- Records are tagged source=manual + markedBy for audit; manual rows are
  flagged with an "M" badge in the grid and Reports, and a Source column is
  added to the xlsx/pdf exports. Scan rows are tagged source=scan.
- Scoped by role (mark_attendance): PE/Supervisor limited to their site,
  PM to their sites, Management/HR all. IST times; day-shift validation
  (Out must be after In).
- Attendance nav item flipped ready=true.

Verified: npm run build; e2e attendance(12); station/overtime/reports/
hierarchy regression all pass.

